00:24:56,619 --> 00:24:58,586
Didn't want to regret it later?

269
00:24:58,708 --> 00:24:59,734
Yeah.

270
00:25:01,316 --> 00:25:02,969
What if...

271
00:25:04,308 --> 00:25:06,463
What if you're bound to regret it either way?

272
00:25:08,636 --> 00:25:10,750
Bound to regret it either way?

273
00:25:14,560 --> 00:25:16,080
What do you mean?

274
00:25:18,090 --> 00:25:19,285
Never mind.

275
00:25:22,742 --> 00:25:25,599
My mom used to say,

276
00:25:26,293 --> 00:25:29,736
if you have to choose between what is right and what you like,

277
00:25:29,890 --> 00:25:31,660
choose what you like first.

278
00:25:32,532 --> 00:25:34,154
Wanna know why?

279
00:25:36,129 --> 00:25:38,696
Because if you choose what you like,

280
00:25:38,697 --> 00:25:40,526
at least it's good for your heart.

281
00:25:43,389 --> 00:25:45,598
What my mom meant was,

282
00:25:45,599 --> 00:25:48,475
we need to be much kinder to ourselves.

283
00:25:49,281 --> 00:25:50,820
I think that's true.

284
00:25:52,798 --> 00:25:54,444
I'm jealous of you.

285
00:25:55,541 --> 00:25:57,166
Your mom is so lovely.

286
00:25:58,634 --> 00:26:00,222
My mom has a lot of quotes.

287
00:26:06,314 --> 00:26:07,634
Thank you, Jane.

288
00:26:08,309 --> 00:26:09,773
No need to thank me.

289
00:26:09,774 --> 00:26:12,725
Just remember to be kind to yourself.

290
00:26:18,286 --> 00:26:19,586
It melts so fast.

291
00:26:21,157 --> 00:26:26,726
The Little Prince learned that "to tame" is to establish ties.

292
00:26:26,727 --> 00:26:30,389
After the Little Prince met the fox,

293
00:26:30,987 --> 00:26:35,459
the fox told him that if he tamed it,

294
00:26:35,460 --> 00:26:40,587
its boring life of hunting chickens every day

295
00:26:40,588 --> 00:26:43,861
would become as bright as the sun.

296
00:26:44,685 --> 00:26:50,100
The fox would recognize the sound of his footsteps,

297
00:26:50,957 --> 00:26:53,846
and would not run away when it heard them.

298
00:26:54,581 --> 00:26:56,983
An ordinary wheat field

299
00:26:58,319 --> 00:27:00,966
would make the fox...

300
00:27:24,630 --> 00:27:26,394
Did Earn forget?

301
00:27:43,580 --> 00:27:44,613
Earn.

302
00:27:45,312 --> 00:27:46,333
Earn.

303
00:28:25,302 --> 00:28:26,954
You can sit next to me.

304
00:28:26,955 --> 00:28:30,481
I might be weird, but at least I'm not a jerk.

305
00:28:31,613 --> 00:28:33,027
And...

306
00:28:33,253 --> 00:28:35,606
I've never seen you as a bad person either.

307
00:28:37,168 --> 00:28:40,856
We know best what kind of person we are.

308
00:28:41,511 --> 00:28:42,838
Ever heard of that?

309
00:28:46,317 --> 00:28:47,712
You can do it.

310
00:28:48,122 --> 00:28:49,853
Don't lose to second place.

311
00:28:52,759 --> 00:28:56,938
I think you might need to lean in a bit closer.

312
00:28:59,636 --> 00:29:02,136
It looks sexier.

313
00:29:25,282 --> 00:29:26,456
You got this?

314
00:29:26,889 --> 00:29:27,922
Earn.

315
00:29:34,241 --> 00:29:36,865
What is essential is invisible to the eye.

316
00:29:38,148 --> 00:29:42,539
It is only with the heart that one can see rightly.

317
00:29:42,933 --> 00:29:48,006
The Little Prince realized that his rose was important.

318
00:29:48,534 --> 00:29:52,153
Because she was the only one.

319
00:29:52,962 --> 00:29:56,120
That he had formed a bond with.

320
00:29:56,121 --> 00:29:58,506
Even if they had to be apart.

321
00:30:01,177 --> 00:30:06,052
This rose would still be the only one.

322
00:30:06,533 --> 00:30:08,489
That was always special to the Little Prince.

323
00:30:08,490 --> 00:30:17,644
The Little Prince might have thought that the bond gave the fox nothing at all.

324
00:30:17,868 --> 00:30:24,898
And even brought tears on the day they had to part.

325
00:30:25,579 --> 00:30:28,290
But in the eyes of the fox.

326
00:30:28,291 --> 00:30:32,311
Its secret is hidden in this truth.

327
00:30:32,940 --> 00:30:35,612
What is essential is invisible to the eye.

328
00:30:38,804 --> 00:30:42,824
It is only with the heart that one can see rightly.

329
00:30:43,064 --> 00:30:46,351
So every bond that is created.

330
00:30:46,352 --> 00:30:52,152
Will be a thread that ties our hearts, making us responsible for each other.

331
00:30:52,481 --> 00:30:54,147
Thank you.

332
00:31:07,805 --> 00:31:10,151
And for the first prize,

333
00:31:10,152 --> 00:31:12,523
I would like to announce the two schools

334
00:31:12,524 --> 00:31:16,069
nominated for the first prize. They are...

335
00:31:16,069 --> 00:31:19,176
Phraharuthai Metta School

336
00:31:19,176 --> 00:31:21,097
and Anna Patronage Tipwan School!

337
00:31:21,098 --> 00:31:23,660
Please come up to the stage.

338
00:31:34,919 --> 00:31:38,152
And the winner of the first prize is...

339
00:31:38,153 --> 00:31:40,706
Congratulations to...

340
00:31:40,706 --> 00:31:42,977
Miss Oranichaporn Ruammitr

341
00:31:42,977 --> 00:31:45,979
from Anna Patronage Tipwan School!

342
00:31:52,997 --> 00:31:55,310
Let's give her another round of applause!

343
00:32:28,117 --> 00:32:31,140
I won because of you, Belle.

344
00:32:31,293 --> 00:32:32,860
Thank you.

345
00:32:33,561 --> 00:32:34,901
You're exaggerating.

346
00:32:35,268 --> 00:32:38,089
You won because you tried your best.

347
00:32:40,408 --> 00:32:42,963
Good girl, Earn.

348
00:32:43,562 --> 00:32:45,695
Why do I feel like a dog?

349
00:32:50,276 --> 00:32:52,658
Here, your reward.

350
00:33:00,026 --> 00:33:02,706
I wanted to buy it to cheer myself up before the competition.

351
00:33:07,516 --> 00:33:08,976
I'll take this one.

352
00:33:15,996 --> 00:33:17,546
Wow.

353
00:33:18,146 --> 00:33:20,117
When did you buy this?

354
00:33:20,118 --> 00:33:21,913
Thank you!

355
00:33:23,268 --> 00:33:24,688
It's so cute.

356
00:33:26,906 --> 00:33:28,816
Skipped class and came a long way, Belle.

357
00:33:32,628 --> 00:33:35,510
I'm not mad. It's good that you came to cheer for your friend.

358
00:33:36,518 --> 00:33:40,333
But next time, take a car. Riding a motorcycle is too hot.

359
00:33:44,673 --> 00:33:49,281
Tomorrow night, I'm throwing a party at my house. You guys should come.

360
00:33:50,542 --> 00:33:54,524
Consider it a thank you for everyone's hard work.

361
00:34:05,306 --> 00:34:07,200
Supplies are here!

362
00:34:25,548 --> 00:34:27,414
I'm sorry about earlier.

363
00:34:27,621 --> 00:34:29,094
For being so harsh on you.

364
00:34:30,229 --> 00:34:31,489
It's okay.

365
00:34:31,490 --> 00:34:34,903
I already know you have a bad mouth.

366
00:34:36,565 --> 00:34:37,931
Just kidding.

367
00:34:44,818 --> 00:34:47,360
I don't know if you've checked the hashtag lately.

368
00:34:47,907 --> 00:34:49,230
But...

369
00:34:49,231 --> 00:34:51,946
I think things are starting to get out of hand.

370
00:34:52,346 --> 00:34:56,186
If you don't do something, I'm sure it'll reach the Mother Superior.

371
00:34:57,290 --> 00:34:58,730
I think so too.

372
00:35:01,788 --> 00:35:04,132
Figured out how to fix it yet?

373
00:35:04,439 --> 00:35:05,945
Probably your idea.

374
00:35:06,572 --> 00:35:08,458
Selling the stuff I have.

375
00:35:11,701 --> 00:35:13,435
Good thinking.

376
00:35:13,730 --> 00:35:17,875
For someone like you, saving up to buy these things again later won't be hard.

377
00:35:20,015 --> 00:35:22,487
Come on, let's start.

378
00:35:22,488 --> 00:35:23,993
Which one first?

379
00:35:25,021 --> 00:35:27,430
Let's see, which one should we do?

380
00:35:27,431 --> 00:35:29,509
That one, or the one in the middle?

381
00:35:29,510 --> 00:35:31,036
Let me get up and take a look.

382
00:35:31,037 --> 00:35:33,523
Let's see. What do we have here?

383
00:35:37,028 --> 00:35:38,160
Wow.

384
00:35:39,228 --> 00:35:41,217
Just one person, but you have like 10 bags.

385
00:35:41,218 --> 00:35:43,119
Oh, this one is pretty.

386
00:35:43,120 --> 00:35:46,018
Here, I'll take a picture. Wear it like this.

387
00:35:48,260 --> 00:35:49,914
This one, this one. Let's take 3 of them.

388
00:36:05,597 --> 00:36:09,064
And the Best Cheer Stand award this year goes to...

389
00:36:09,065 --> 00:36:12,004
The Green Team!

390
00:36:29,358 --> 00:36:30,398
Mom.

391
00:36:30,593 --> 00:36:32,888
I took the kids to the competition and we won first place.

392
00:36:34,243 --> 00:36:35,390
Really?

393
00:36:38,195 --> 00:36:39,841
That's amazing, sweetie.

394
00:36:43,913 --> 00:36:46,595
So you don't have to worry about the medical bills anymore.

395
00:36:47,581 --> 00:36:48,788
Nalin.

396
00:36:51,303 --> 00:36:53,331
Can we talk for a bit?

397
00:37:09,197 --> 00:37:10,683
What is it, Mom?

398
00:37:14,151 --> 00:37:15,311
Nalin.

399
00:37:16,372 --> 00:37:18,152
Mom is so tired.

400
00:37:20,356 --> 00:37:22,096
I already told the doctor.

401
00:37:23,235 --> 00:37:25,410
That I want to stop the treatment.

402
00:37:36,328 --> 00:37:38,075
I'm sorry, sweetie.

403
00:37:44,449 --> 00:37:45,915
I'm sorry.

404
00:37:57,840 --> 00:37:59,741
It's okay, Mom.

405
00:38:01,805 --> 00:38:02,994
I'm okay.

406
00:38:09,426 --> 00:38:11,596
You don't have to cry anymore.

407
00:38:17,571 --> 00:38:19,118
I loves you, sweetie.

408
00:39:06,982 --> 00:39:08,088
Hey, hey!

409
00:39:08,089 --> 00:39:09,828
Someone just messaged to buy it.

410
00:39:10,235 --> 00:39:11,543
Really? Let me see.

411
00:39:13,274 --> 00:39:16,393
[Can you lower the price a bit more? It looks pretty worn out.]

412
00:39:16,534 --> 00:39:19,102
"Can you lower the price a bit more? It looks pretty worn out."

413
00:39:19,330 --> 00:39:21,184
Oh, please.

414
00:39:21,230 --> 00:39:22,959
This bag is worth over a hundred thousand.

415
00:39:23,383 --> 00:39:25,087
Haggling this much, why not just ask for it for free?

416
00:39:28,306 --> 00:39:30,308
You don't have to sell it yet, you know.

417
00:39:30,309 --> 00:39:32,640
I'll help boost the post in case someone else asks.

418
00:39:35,552 --> 00:39:38,825
[If you're ready, you can transfer the money now.]

419
00:39:40,722 --> 00:39:41,997
It's fine.

420
00:39:42,277 --> 00:39:45,043
Selling this one bag can pay off several people.

421
00:39:45,270 --> 00:39:47,365
It's better to get the money and fix the problem first.

422
00:39:47,968 --> 00:39:51,462
Aww, good job, little Nano.

423
00:39:51,463 --> 00:39:52,933
Do we look like we're just playing around?

424
00:39:52,934 --> 00:39:55,107
Nano did great. Great job.

425
00:40:21,655 --> 00:40:22,986
Hello, Jane.

426
00:40:22,987 --> 00:40:24,266
Hello, Earn.

427
00:40:24,267 --> 00:40:27,848
Teacher Nalin is throwing a party at her house today. Do you wanna come?

428
00:40:27,849 --> 00:40:30,995
Hey, I'm in. But can I bring Nano too?

429
00:40:30,996 --> 00:40:32,645
Yeah, sure.

430
00:40:32,647 --> 00:40:34,379
Okay, see you then.

431
00:40:34,380 --> 00:40:36,243
Okay, see you.

432
00:40:40,255 --> 00:40:41,512
Oh.

433
00:40:41,899 --> 00:40:43,920
Inviting people over... did you ask for permission yet?

434
00:40:45,599 --> 00:40:49,368
Teacher Nalin, can I invite some more friends over?

435
00:40:50,465 --> 00:40:53,144
Inviting them before asking? Sure.

436
00:40:54,095 --> 00:40:55,188
Thank you.

437
00:40:55,554 --> 00:40:58,697
Teacher, can I invite my friends from the science class too?

438
00:40:58,698 --> 00:40:59,623
Yes, you can.

439
00:40:59,624 --> 00:41:01,106
Thank you.

440
00:41:18,455 --> 00:41:20,108
It's like that.

441
00:41:20,109 --> 00:41:21,162
6 pieces.

442
00:41:25,019 --> 00:41:26,285
Keep going!

443
00:41:29,816 --> 00:41:31,616
We're here!

444
00:41:31,617 --> 00:41:33,177
Hello, Teacher Nalin.

445
00:41:33,178 --> 00:41:35,900
Come on in.

446
00:41:36,917 --> 00:41:38,524
Come sit with us.

447
00:41:39,977 --> 00:41:41,884
Wow, so many snacks.

448
00:41:41,885 --> 00:41:42,912
Can I eat this?

449
00:41:42,913 --> 00:41:44,380
Sure, go ahead.

450
00:41:47,702 --> 00:41:48,802
Hey, Amy.

451
00:41:49,475 --> 00:41:51,048
Ooh, who did you come with?

452
00:41:51,049 --> 00:41:52,224
Who's that with you?

453
00:41:53,408 --> 00:41:56,708
That person, of course. Don't you know?

454
00:41:57,495 --> 00:41:59,787
Turns out it's just a minor bone fracture.

455
00:41:59,788 --> 00:42:02,527
The person who brought it in said it got run over.

456
00:42:02,939 --> 00:42:06,264
I was so shocked, but it was just a scrape.

457
00:42:13,186 --> 00:42:20,838
[Nano, when are you paying me back?]

458
00:42:21,904 --> 00:42:24,401
I think you should close the fundraiser now, Nano.

459
00:42:24,402 --> 00:42:26,068
The amount should be enough now.

460
00:42:29,967 --> 00:42:33,763
Doctor, I have to go now. My friends are waiting for me.

461
00:42:43,372 --> 00:42:44,585
Amy, wanna play with us?

462
00:42:45,620 --> 00:42:47,542
Okay, sure.

463
00:42:53,809 --> 00:42:54,956
Can I have some too?

464
00:42:55,302 --> 00:42:56,436
Sure.

465
00:42:56,699 --> 00:42:59,301
Whoever loses is paying.

466
00:43:00,109 --> 00:43:01,877
I'm going to the restroom real quick.

467
00:43:16,334 --> 00:43:18,283
Anyone want to have some more fun?

468
00:43:18,284 --> 00:43:19,944
Whoa, P'Som!

469
00:44:35,621 --> 00:44:36,980
Teacher.

470
00:44:37,585 --> 00:44:38,912
Are you okay?

471
00:44:42,049 --> 00:44:43,542
There are so many people downstairs.

472
00:44:47,867 --> 00:44:49,522
It's a party, of course there are a lot of people.

473
00:44:50,222 --> 00:44:51,870
For me, a party...

474
00:44:52,268 --> 00:44:54,063
can be just two people.

475
00:44:57,199 --> 00:44:58,559
Can I have a drink too?

476
00:44:59,241 --> 00:45:00,161
No.

477
00:45:00,814 --> 00:45:02,907
You're still a kid. You can't drink.

478
00:45:04,911 --> 00:45:06,910
And when was your first drink?

479
00:45:08,245 --> 00:45:09,359
10th grade.

480
00:45:10,213 --> 00:45:13,013
See? And you're lecturing me.

481
00:45:24,533 --> 00:45:26,093
I thought you weren't coming.

482
00:45:27,658 --> 00:45:30,313
I can't come to a party without bringing some snacks, right?

483
00:45:31,668 --> 00:45:33,002
So...

484
00:45:33,228 --> 00:45:34,755
who else is here?

485
00:45:37,373 --> 00:45:39,657
You've already paid everyone back.

486
00:45:39,658 --> 00:45:42,134
Why worry? It's going to be fine.

487
00:45:42,547 --> 00:45:45,049
If anyone gives you a hard time, I'll slap them for you.

488
00:45:45,684 --> 00:45:46,917
Slap them?

489
00:45:47,679 --> 00:45:48,942
Clap my hands.

490
00:46:01,842 --> 00:46:04,346
Everyone's waiting for you. You're the only one who's late.

491
00:46:04,492 --> 00:46:05,912
Welcome drinks.

492
00:46:07,442 --> 00:46:08,829
Have a sip.

493
00:46:12,683 --> 00:46:14,296
It's a bit weak.

494
00:46:15,595 --> 00:46:17,608
Wow, is this alcohol?

495
00:46:17,608 --> 00:46:19,061
This is my first time.

496
00:46:22,080 --> 00:46:24,568
I'm glad to be your first.

497
00:46:25,724 --> 00:46:27,672
Come on, let's go inside.

498
00:46:29,909 --> 00:46:31,122
Cheers.

499
00:46:32,537 --> 00:46:35,687
Come on, cheers!

500
00:46:39,317 --> 00:46:40,293
Anyone wanna play a game?

501
00:46:40,294 --> 00:46:41,927
Let's play a game!

502
00:46:42,321 --> 00:46:45,504
What's going on with you two?

503
00:46:45,505 --> 00:46:49,191
What's the deal?

504
00:46:49,706 --> 00:46:51,309
P'Amy.

505
00:46:54,586 --> 00:46:56,979
Will you be my girlfriend?

506
00:46:58,668 --> 00:47:05,366
Say yes! Say yes! Say yes!

507
00:47:05,367 --> 00:47:06,960
No...

508
00:47:11,735 --> 00:47:13,962
I can't let Aioon be the one to ask.

509
00:47:17,615 --> 00:47:20,255
So... Aioon, will you be my girlfriend?

510
00:47:43,417 --> 00:47:44,617
Hey.

511
00:47:46,645 --> 00:47:48,493
Even though this isn't the rooftop,

512
00:47:49,632 --> 00:47:51,769
if there's anything on your mind, you can tell me.

513
00:48:06,643 --> 00:48:07,696
It's nothing.

514
00:48:23,176 --> 00:48:25,816
[Hey, Mink posted a photo of a marriage proposal.]
[Friends are sharing it everywhere.]

515
00:48:38,988 --> 00:48:40,543
What kind of crazy day is this?

516
00:48:42,073 --> 00:48:43,280
What happened?

517
00:48:55,546 --> 00:48:57,826
Why is life so tiring?

518
00:49:00,632 --> 00:49:04,669
Well, we're tired because we're not dead yet.

519
00:49:16,112 --> 00:49:18,578
I don't know what you're going through,

520
00:49:19,804 --> 00:49:21,410
but I'm here for you.

521
00:49:23,814 --> 00:49:25,196
Always ready to listen.

522
00:49:31,714 --> 00:49:32,794
Thank you.

523
00:49:48,762 --> 00:49:50,547
My eyes are as swollen as a frog's.

524
00:49:50,548 --> 00:49:51,682
Let me see.

525
00:49:53,214 --> 00:49:55,682
They're not swollen at all. You look beautiful.

526
00:49:55,984 --> 00:49:57,164
Here.

527
00:49:57,604 --> 00:49:59,252
Why did you take a picture? It's ugly.

528
00:49:59,843 --> 00:50:01,010
You're beautiful.

529
00:50:01,503 --> 00:50:03,158
Beautiful even when you cry.

530
00:50:15,314 --> 00:50:16,480
Here.

531
00:50:18,121 --> 00:50:21,430
I saw it and thought of you, so I bought it for you.

532
00:50:28,734 --> 00:50:30,187
I'll take this one too, please.

533
00:50:30,188 --> 00:50:31,344
Sure.

534
00:50:59,088 --> 00:51:00,549
I think...

535
00:51:07,580 --> 00:51:09,034
I like you.

